The Liverpool keeper spent all last year on loan at Napoli and though Rafa Benitez would be keen to have him back in Serie A next season, Liverpool would prefer him to have a permanent move so they do not have to keep subsidising his wages.

Napoli also have Brazilian keeper Rafael developing well and are keen to spend their budget in other areas.

Wenger tried to sign Reina in 2010 when Arsenal bid £20m but Liverpool refused to sell him at the time.

